   "cell_type": "raw",
   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m001\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# NPS Driver Analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Project Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"This notebook analyzes NPS (Net Promoter Score) survey results and supporting customer features to understand what differentiates promoters, passives, and detractors.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Learning Objectives\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Calculate and interpret NPS from raw survey responses.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Profile promoters, passives, and detractors across customer dimensions.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Identify the strongest drivers of high/low NPS.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Generate actionable recommendations to improve NPS.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Business / Research Problem\\n\",\n",
    "    \"NPS is a widely used loyalty metric, but the score alone doesn't explain *why* customers feel the way they do. Driver analysis connects NPS to actionable levers.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Why This Analysis Matters\\n\",\n",
    "    \"A 10-point NPS improvement is associated with 10-15% revenue growth in many industries. Understanding drivers enables targeted improvements.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m002\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Overview\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Synthetic dataset of **2,500 NPS survey responses** with customer attributes and satisfaction sub-scores.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Dataset Source and License Notes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Synthetically generated for educational purposes.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c001\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for pkg in [\\\"pandas\\\", \\\"numpy\\\", \\\"matplotlib\\\", \\\"seaborn\\\", \\\"scipy\\\"]:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    try:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        importlib.import_module(pkg)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    except ImportError:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        subprocess.check_call([sys.executable, \\\"-m\\\", \\\"pip\\\", \\\"install\\\", \\\"-q\\\", pkg])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Environment ready.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c002\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import numpy as np\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import pandas as pd\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import seaborn as sns\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from scipy import stats\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import warnings\\n\",\n",
    "    \"warnings.filterwarnings(\\\"ignore\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sns.set_style(\\\"whitegrid\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"%matplotlib inline\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c003\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"SEED = 42\\n\",\n",
    "    \"N = 2500\\n\",\n",
    "    \"SEGMENTS = [\\\"SMB\\\", \\\"Mid-Market\\\", \\\"Enterprise\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"INDUSTRIES = [\\\"Tech\\\", \\\"Finance\\\", \\\"Healthcare\\\", \\\"Retail\\\", \\\"Manufacturing\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Configuration loaded.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c004\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"rng = np.random.default_rng(SEED)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"rows = []\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for i in range(N):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    segment = rng.choice(SEGMENTS, p=[0.40, 0.35, 0.25])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    industry = rng.choice(INDUSTRIES)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    tenure = int(rng.exponential(10) + 1)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    # Sub-scores (1-10)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    product_quality = np.clip(int(rng.normal(7, 1.5)), 1, 10)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    support_quality = np.clip(int(rng.normal(6.5, 2)), 1, 10)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    ease_of_use = np.clip(int(rng.normal(7.2, 1.3)), 1, 10)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    value_for_money = np.clip(int(rng.normal(6, 1.8)), 1, 10)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    # NPS score (0-10) based on sub-scores\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    base = (product_quality * 0.3 + support_quality * 0.25 + ease_of_use * 0.2 + value_for_money * 0.25)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    nps_score = np.clip(int(base + rng.normal(0, 1)), 0, 10)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    nps_category = \\\"Promoter\\\" if nps_score >= 9 else \\\"Passive\\\" if nps_score >= 7 else \\\"Detractor\\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    rows.append({\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"respondent_id\\\": f\\\"R{i+1:05d}\\\", \\\"segment\\\": segment, \\\"industry\\\": industry,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"tenure_months\\\": tenure, \\\"product_quality\\\": product_quality,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"support_quality\\\": support_quality, \\\"ease_of_use\\\": ease_of_use,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\\"value_for_money\\\": value_for_money, \\\"nps_score\\\": nps_score, \\\"nps_category\\\": nps_category,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    })\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df = pd.DataFrame(rows)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Dataset: {df.shape}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df.head()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c005\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Calculate NPS\\n\",\n",
    "    \"promoters = (df[\\\"nps_category\\\"] == \\\"Promoter\\\").sum()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"detractors = (df[\\\"nps_category\\\"] == \\\"Detractor\\\").sum()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"nps = (promoters - detractors) / len(df) * 100\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Promoters: {promoters} ({promoters/len(df):.1%})\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Passives: {(df['nps_category']=='Passive').sum()} ({(df['nps_category']=='Passive').mean():.1%})\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Detractors: {detractors} ({detractors/len(df):.1%})\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"\\\\n🎯 NPS = {nps:.1f}\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c006\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df[\\\"nps_score\\\"].value_counts().sort_index().plot(kind=\\\"bar\\\", ax=axes[0], color=\\\"steelblue\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_title(\\\"NPS Score Distribution\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"colors = {\\\"Promoter\\\": \\\"#2ecc71\\\", \\\"Passive\\\": \\\"#f39c12\\\", \\\"Detractor\\\": \\\"#e74c3c\\\"}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"df[\\\"nps_category\\\"].value_counts().reindex([\\\"Promoter\\\", \\\"Passive\\\", \\\"Detractor\\\"]).plot(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    kind=\\\"bar\\\", ax=axes[1], color=[colors[c] for c in [\\\"Promoter\\\", \\\"Passive\\\", \\\"Detractor\\\"]])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].set_title(\\\"NPS Category Distribution\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].tick_params(axis=\\\"x\\\", rotation=0)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m003\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Driver Analysis: What differentiates Promoters from Detractors?\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c007\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"driver_cols = [\\\"product_quality\\\", \\\"support_quality\\\", \\\"ease_of_use\\\", \\\"value_for_money\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"driver_by_cat = df.groupby(\\\"nps_category\\\")[driver_cols].mean().reindex([\\\"Promoter\\\", \\\"Passive\\\", \\\"Detractor\\\"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"=== Average Sub-Scores by NPS Category ===\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(driver_by_cat.round(2))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"driver_by_cat.T.plot(kind=\\\"bar\\\", ax=ax, color=[\\\"#2ecc71\\\", \\\"#f39c12\\\", \\\"#e74c3c\\\"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_title(\\\"Sub-Score Comparison: Promoters vs Passives vs Detractors\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_ylabel(\\\"Average Score (1-10)\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.tick_params(axis=\\\"x\\\", rotation=15)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c008\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Correlation of sub-scores with NPS\\n\",\n",
    "    \"corr_with_nps = df[driver_cols + [\\\"nps_score\\\"]].corr()[\\\"nps_score\\\"].drop(\\\"nps_score\\\").sort_values(ascending=False)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 4))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"corr_with_nps.plot(kind=\\\"barh\\\", ax=ax, color=\\\"steelblue\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_title(\\\"Sub-Score Correlation with NPS\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.set_xlabel(\\\"Pearson r\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m004\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## NPS by Segment and Industry\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"id\": \"c009\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"def calc_nps(group):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    p = (group == \\\"Promoter\\\").sum()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    d = (group == \\\"Detractor\\\").sum()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    return (p - d) / len(group) * 100\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"nps_by_seg = df.groupby(\\\"segment\\\")[\\\"nps_category\\\"].apply(calc_nps).sort_values(ascending=False)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"nps_by_ind = df.groupby(\\\"industry\\\")[\\\"nps_category\\\"].apply(calc_nps).sort_values(ascending=False)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 5))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"nps_by_seg.plot(kind=\\\"bar\\\", ax=axes[0], color=\\\"seagreen\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_title(\\\"NPS by Segment\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].axhline(0, color=\\\"red\\\", ls=\\\"--\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].tick_params(axis=\\\"x\\\", rotation=0)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"nps_by_ind.plot(kind=\\\"bar\\\", ax=axes[1], color=\\\"coral\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].set_title(\\\"NPS by Industry\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].axhline(0, color=\\\"red\\\", ls=\\\"--\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].tick_params(axis=\\\"x\\\", rotation=30)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"id\": \"m005\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## Key Findings\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Value for money and support quality show the largest gap** between promoters and detractors — these are the biggest improvement levers.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Product quality has the strongest correlation with NPS** — the core product experience matters most.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **NPS varies by segment,** with Enterprise customers often showing different patterns than SMB.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Passives are the swing group** — converting even 20% of passives to promoters would significantly lift NPS.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Limitations\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Synthetic data; real NPS data has more response bias.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Sub-scores are correlated with each other, making driver isolation difficult.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- No open-ended response analysis.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Recommendations / Next Steps\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Invest in support quality improvement — it's the most actionable driver gap.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Address value perception through pricing transparency or feature communication.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Follow up with passives (NPS 7-8) to understand what would make them promoters.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. Segment NPS reporting by industry and segment for targeted action plans.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Common Mistakes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Tracking NPS as a single number without understanding drivers.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Ignoring passives — they're easier to convert than detractors.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Comparing NPS across industries without benchmarks.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. Not closing the feedback loop with respondents.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Mini Challenge / Exercises\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Build a logistic regression to predict Promoter vs Detractor.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Create a Promoter→Detractor risk matrix by segment × industry.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Simulate the NPS impact of improving support quality by 1 point.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. Design a follow-up survey for passive respondents.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Final Summary / Key Takeaways\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **NPS driver analysis is essential** — the score alone is not actionable.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Product quality and value for money are the strongest NPS drivers.**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Support quality has the most room for improvement** and the largest promoter/detractor gap.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Segment-level NPS reveals hidden patterns** masked by the aggregate score.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  }\n",
    " ],\n",
